Tailwind: "you get the ergonomics of inline with the full power of css"

- you don't have to create classes there are predifined
  names that tells how the element will be styled
- in css class defined, I have to go to the class to know what does the class do to the element

- useState: Lets a component "remember" values between renders.

- useeffect: tells React: "Do something after the component shows up on the screen."
  useEffect(() => {
  // Your code here (the effect)
  }, [dependencies]); dependencies-> when it changes, run whats inside useeffect, if it is empty then only run it once when (onMount)
